	In article &lt;1990Feb7.173439.29059@IDA.ORG&gt;, stoltz@IDA.ORG (Bill Stoltz) writes:
	&gt; Can someone tell me why sendmail would not be able to resolve a
	&gt; host name, but nslookup can?
	&gt; I am running SunOS 4.0.3 and Sendmail with MX support 

	Bill, I noticed the same problem on my Sun running 4.0.3 and
	I'm not running DNS...  I thought something was broken in
	YP...   But then I tried the xview/mailtool and had no trouble
	finding the hosts....     I suspect the lookup problem is not
	in sendmail or DNS, but is in the sunview/mailtool, but I can't
	be sure....

Eh, both the SunView and XView mailtool use '/usr/ucb/Mail' as
a backend interface.  So there's no real difference in the
way either of them 'use' DNS and/or YP (eh, NIS).

Just so this isn't a complete waste of time, is anyone
doing anything 'interesting' with MB/MG records yet?

Jim

